value.title: 'Lack standing': Rep. Gohmert's lawsuit against Pence to overturn election results thrown out
value.excerpt: U.S. District Court Judge Jeremy Kernodle, a Trump appointee, said Rep. Louie Gohmert and a group of other Republicans on the lawsuit "lack standing."

value.title: Trump vetoes Calif. fishing bill over seafood trade deficit
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has vetoed a bill that would have gradually ended the use of large-mesh drift gillnets used exclusively in federal waters off the coast of California

value.title: President Trump says South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem should challenge 'RINO' Sen. John Thune in 2022
value.excerpt: Thune drew Trump’s ire in recent days after he criticized the president’s bid to challenge the results of the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Mike Pence seeks dismissal of lawsuit aiming to give him the power to overturn election loss
value.excerpt: The Justice Department has asked to dismiss a lawsuit led by a House Republican that seeks to give Mike Pence power to overturn the election.

value.title: What Will Pence Do When Congress Counts the Votes?
value.excerpt: Readers are shocked that the question is being asked and speculate that the vice president may find an excuse not to be present. They also criticize Senator Josh Hawley.

value.title: Mike Pence heading to Georgia on Monday ahead of runoff elections
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is heading to Georgia on Monday to campaign ahead of Tuesday’s critical U.S. Senate runoff elections.

value.title: With Trump a no-show, Mar-a-Lago guests left to party maskless with Rudy Giuliani and Vanilla Ice
value.excerpt: Guests who paid four-figures for tickets to President Donald Trump's annual New Year's Eve party were left to party with his personal attorney Rudy Giuliani, his two adult sons and various figures from the conservative media — none of whom wore masks — after the President made a last-minute decision

value.title: Fact check: President Trump spent Thanksgiving with troops in Afghanistan in 2019, not 2020
value.excerpt: Social media users having been sharing posts that claim President Donald Trump spent Thanksgiving 2020 with troops in Bagram, Afghanistan, not playing golf. This claim is false: the photo of Trump in Bagram is from 2019.

value.title: 'Dangerous ploy': GOP Sen. Ben Sasse slams efforts by Trump, Hawley to overturn election
value.excerpt: Nebraska Republican Sen. Ben Sasse denounced the "institutional arsonist members of Congress who will object to the Electoral College vote."

value.title: Joe Biden, Nancy Pelosi to Draw on Their History in Bid to Unite Fractious Democrats
value.excerpt: The president-elect and House speaker share the job of steering a divided Democratic coalition amid a pandemic and an economy recovering from a deep slump.

value.title: Trump attacks and vote by mail: the top voting rights stories of 2020
value.excerpt: The pandemic created new barriers to the ballot box and strengthened existing ones – aided by the president and his Republican allies

value.title: Trump reflects on his 'historic victories' in new year message
value.excerpt: Biden looks ahead to 2021 in upbeat message as Trump points out he correctly predicted arrival of vaccine before year’s end

value.title: Biden inauguration events to include coronavirus victims vigil at Lincoln Memorial
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden’s plans to include a lighting ceremony honoring the more than 341,000 Americans who have died from the coronavirus as part of the events leading up to his inauguration.

value.title: From covfefe to the Mooch: 10 funny moments from the Trump presidency
value.excerpt: Amid four years of corruption, caging children and trashing democracy there were some light-hearted moments – no really

value.title: Trump reportedly lashed out at Kushner over increased COVID-19 testing: 'I'm going to lose, and it's going to be your fault'
value.excerpt: Trump reportedly told Kushner, "I want to do what Mexico does. They don't give you a test till you get to the emergency room and you're vomiting."

value.title: Trump extends restrictions on work visas, says coronavirus pandemic still disrupts 'American livelihoods'
value.excerpt: The order will now expire at the end of March, extending into President-elect Joe Biden’s first term in office.

value.title: Amid election turmoil caused by Trump, Chief Justice Roberts lauds judiciary for pandemic response
value.excerpt: Roberts notably avoided any mention of the judiciary's other historic challenges caused in large part by President Donald Trump, his frequent nemesis.

value.title: Can Donald Trump Pass $2,000 Stimulus Checks by Executive Order?
value.excerpt: With a standalone bill that would allow $2,000 stimulus checks apparently dead in the Senate, could President Donald Trump sign an executive order that would allow the higher direct payments to reach Americans?

value.title: Trump budget director accuses Biden team of 'false statements' in latest transition spat
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's budget director is accusing President-elect Joe Biden's team of issuing "false statements" regarding his office's cooperation during the ongoing transition, insisting the office has been fully transparent over the course of 45 meetings.

value.title: Joe Biden's Approach to Latin America Will Be Major Departure from Donald Trump
value.excerpt: Joe Biden believes, and he has for years, that conditions must be improved in Latin America if the United States wants to slow immigration. A less antagonistic U.S. approach is coming.

value.title: One of Trump's 'biggest services to America' was exposing liberal media: Jeffrey Lord
value.excerpt: One of President Trump's top accomplishments came not on the domestic policy or foreign policy front, but in simply exposing left-wing media figures for their biases, columnist and political analyst Jeffrey Lord said Wednesday on "The Ingraham Angle."

value.title: Computer repairman: Twitter calling me hacker in Hunter Biden laptop case was 'death sentence'
value.excerpt: The computer repairman at the center of the Hunter Biden laptop story said Thursday that Twitter destroyed his business by labeling him a "hacker" and legal action was his only recourse.

value.title: Biden inauguration to feature memorial for COVID victims
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is planning a lighting ceremony at the Lincoln Memorial Reflecting Pool to honor those killed by the coronavirus the day before he is sworn into office on Jan. 20

value.title: Live politics updates: Trump to return to DC early, GOP senator says he's 'playing with fire' in contesting election
value.excerpt: Sasse said the effort by Trump and his allies to overturn Biden's win amounted to pointing a "loaded gun at the heart of legitimate self-government."

value.title: Biden's inaugural committee hosting national memorial for Covid-19 victims on January 19
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's inaugural committee on Thursday announced that it is hosting a national memorial to remember and honor the lives lost to Covid-19 and is asking cities and towns around the country to participate.
